title: Song of Coyote After the Flood
lyrics_translation: I can not walk, I am dragging along, I cried, Ah, Ah!

title: Song of Elder Brother After the Flood
lyrics_translation:
Black refuge where I dwell.
I am going forth with it.
I am there.

title: Song of Elder Brother After He Had Created the Spirits
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
I have created you here, I have created you here
The red evening I bring to you

title: Song of Elder Brother After He Had Created the Wind and Clouds
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation: I suffered to the bottom of my heart but at last I created a great deal of wind and at last I created many clouds, so now I am singing for joy.

title: Song of Earth Magician when Disappearing in the Ground
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation: Here I sink, and I know all sorts of things

title: Song of Brown Buzzard After Killing Elder Brother
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation: I have done the worst thing now in killing you, my brother, but I am going to leave your wind and your clouds

title: Song of Elder Brother After Returning to Life
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation: There is an old man sitting down and fixing his vaäko (canteen), fixing his vaäko

title: Song Concerning the Talking Tree
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.

title: Song Before Emerging from Ashes Hill
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation: Now we are going to look over the world and see what is going on

title: Song After Emerging from Ashes Hill
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
The world we have come into looks so grassy,
We come out to look over the world

title: It is Raven Mountain
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Here we are on our way and see the distant mountain.
See, the mountain far from us that has the cloud is Raven Mountain.

title: White Feathers Along the Edge of the World
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation: Downy white feathers are moving beneath the sunset and along the edge of the world

title: I Have Been in This World a Long Time
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation: Oh! I have seen many things in this world and I have been in this world a long time

title: Song With Which Two Boys Killed Their Grandmother
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Our grandmother says it will be all right that she dies,
Because she has been alive a long time.
That is why she does not mind dying,
Because we can not keep up with the crowd.

title: The World Would Burn Without the Rain
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Now, now I have found what you did,
The world will burn if you do this,
Now i have found it out.

title: Song After the Inhabitants of Casa Grande Were Killed
lyrics_translation:
Good luck, my grandmother.
All that you have done will be sounded through the world.

title: Song That Gave Woman the Strength to Carry the Burden Basket
lyrics_translation:
Going toward the east where the road goes;
Where the burden basket walked.

title: Song of Brown Buzzard After Removing His Scalp
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
You must enjoy yourselves in the evening.
Look at me. See how I look and yet I am happy.

title: See My Scalp Hanging on a Pole
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Get up and dance.
Look up and see the end of the pole where my scalp is hanging. 
I want you to enjoy yourselves.

title: Am I an Eagle?
lyrics_translation:
Am I an eagle?
My feathers are filled with mysterious power.

title: Feather Meal Give Me to Drink
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication

title: My Feathers Are Growing Longer
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication
lyrics: Wanitho [I will become] ci [like] makai [a medicine] coï [man] niäthanur [my feathers] vavazaza [are growing longer]

title: The Eagle Will Destroy Us All
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication
lyrics: Humo [now] kupahaku [the eagle] natho [is made] humo [now] tokiyo [it will destroy us all]

title: He Walked Up the Slippery Rocks
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication
lyrics: Kanina [It was] vavahi [rocks] nahpiöni [slippery] wahpola [arrow shafts] tacai [stick in] koitha [on this] caiimuna [walked up]

title: Song to Overcome Fear
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication
lyrics: Thani [I am] thonai [white] Ethoi [Elder Brother] vavashi [rocks] sithahpiöni [slippery] koina [over this] kaämo [I am] himuna [going]

title: Song to Put the Eagle to Sleep
comments: Densmore also reports another text for the same melody (same page)
lyrics: Mowali [fly] ha [ho]

title: Song of the Old Woman Who Attended Elder Brother
lyrics_translation:
You have done it right, you little bit of an Elder Brother.
Henceforth the villages will be safe and I am on the ground, I will get along better.

title: The Rocks are Making a Noise
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication
lyrics: Vahavi [towering rocks] kohona [sounding] hononi [evening] wuma [with them] iasoakima [I am crying]

title: Song When Restoring a Boy to Life
lyrics_translation: He lies face downward

title: Lamenting the Dead Eagles
lyrics: Hayah [Oh] niroika [my pet]
lyrics_translation: Oh my pet

title: I Will Pull Out Their Feathers
lyrics_translation:
I will take any young birds and raise them.
When their feathers grow long I will put them out.

title: Song After Making the Bows and Arrows
lyrics_translation:
Bows now are made,
Arrows now are made.
Towards the west we will try them.
You can watch them fly, my boys.

title: Four Fires on the Ground
lyrics_translation:
One in the corner, in the square on the ground,
A fire in each corner, four fires on the ground

title: Who is Going to Marry Me?
lyrics_translation:
Who are you, nice boys?
Who is going to marry me?

title: The Girls are Approaching
lyrics_translation:
From the east the girls are approaching.
They came to the place of the singing,
They are here.

title: A Fillet of White Eagle Down
lyrics_translation: I am [...], I am showy, with glittering belt and a fillet of white eagle down

title: Terrible in Its Power to Destroy
lyrics_translation: Hanging motionless in the sky yet terrible in its power to destroy

title: Song to Make the Boy Invisible
lyrics_translation:
My poor grandchild, my poor grandchild,
It is the head gaming stick that always wins, 
Throw it forward

title: The Man Who Has No Joy
lyrics_translation:
Who is the man who killed an enemy and has no joy?
I am having all the joy alone

title: From One Dance Circle to Another
lyrics_translation: Twin girls, they go from one dancing circle to another, returning to the place from which they started

title: Song of the Women by the Sea
lyrics_translation:
Where am I running from, that I come here?
Am I a crazy woman with a painted face?

title: I Will Toss Up the Sticks
lyrics_translation:
Now I toss up the sticks.
I will throw the sticks for the corner.
(The highest score was made by this throw.)

title: It Is Time to Pay Your Wager
lyrics_translation:
The time is come to pay your wager;
The time is come.

title: A White Wind from the West
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1072.0, "meta.bpm": 116.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
From the west a white wind is coming out.
Stand there and look, it is not near,
It is beside the ocean, there you will see it.
By the reflected light of the sun you will see it.

title: The Morning Shines on Manasi Mountain
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1033.0, "meta.bpm": 63.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
The bright morning begins to shine.
Get up, three of you, and see Manasi Mountain.
On top of it there is yellow water,
I went there, drank the water, and staggered in running.

title: Song when Administering Herb Medicine
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1041.0, "meta.bpm": 92.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
Are you going to make a doctor out of me?
You have brought me in here and I see.

title: Sandy Loam Fields
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1036.0, "meta.bpm": 88.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
[Part 1]
Sandy Loam Fields, on top of these lands Elder Brother stands and sings.
Over our heads the clouds are seen, downy white feathers gatherd in a bunch.

[Part 2]
After hearing these songs the women gather on Sandy Loam Fields,
Their heads decorated with clouds of feathers

title: I Will Sit and Sing
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1037.0, "meta.bpm": 160.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
[Part 1]
I am going to sit here and sing, I am going to sit here and sing.
On top of our ground you will see green scum drying op.
(This refers to land on which water has recently been standing)

[Part 2]
I am going to stand here and sing, I am going to stand here and sing.
On top of our ground you will see foam drying up

title: Out of the Mountains
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1038.0, "meta.bpm": 100.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
[Part 1]
That bird comes out back of Frog Mountains.
It stretches its arms trying to reach Cokwigan Mountains (in Mexico).

[Part 2]
A measuring worm comes out of Long Mountains (Santa Rita)
It stretches itself, trying to reach Iohlikum (Queen Mountains, part of Baboquivari rangre).

title: Singing to the Leaves and Flowers
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1039.0, "meta.bpm": 104.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
[Part 1]
Crazy woman, crazy woman, trying to sing to mescal leaves,
How can she sing to them and make the wind come?

[Part 2]
Young children trying to sing to bahwi flowers,
How can they sing to bahwi flowers and bring rain?

title: Toward the Mountains
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1040.0, "meta.bpm": 104.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
[Part 1]
Hanamikan Mountain calls itself doctor and stands by itself.
Toward it I am walking.

[Part 2]
Thatkam calls itself brave, standing toward Hanapkam Mountain.

title: Song of the Badger Medicine
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1024.0, "meta.bpm": 76.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
I know everything in the bottom of my heart,
From coyote I learn all this,
I get it and keep it within me, and hold it there.

title: They Covered Me with Sunshine
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1021.0, "meta.bpm": 69.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Gray horned toad, the sun shines on you.
The susnshine they gathered.
With that they covered me but I got out from it.

title: A Painted Snake Comes Out
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1022.0, "meta.bpm": 69.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Here we begin to talk.
We call a name toward the east and a snake comes out, nicely painted.

title: Song to a Little Yellow Wasp
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1023.0, "meta.bpm": 72.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Little yellow wasp, you throw the dirt in my eyes.
I do not know what to do with you.
All I can do is to make a long-drawn breath, hoping you will die in four days.

title: Brown Lizard
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1042.0, "meta.bpm": 76.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation: He hangs it on both sides of himself and rolls around, then he gets up and dances with these on either side.

title: Song to Cure an Injury by a Horse
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1014.0, "meta.bpm": 92.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
The devil's power shines over us now.
We can see it shine on the tail of a black horse and we can also see the shining on top of every mountain.
We know it will cure you.

title: I Came from the East
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1016.0, "meta.bpm": 104.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
From the east I came half dead with hunger and thirst.
I came to a little water hole but it was dried up.
I knew no other.
I decided to find some other horses or a person who could take me to water.
This boy took me to water but afterwards he treated me badly.

title: You Tied Me with a Black Hair Rope
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1015.0, "meta.bpm": 100.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
Black hair rope is what you used in roping me.
You treated me badly.
You even threw me down and tied me.
Not satisfied with that, you tied a knot in the end of my tail.
That made me disgusted.

title: Song of a Black Horse
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1017.0, "meta.bpm": 104.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation: I could go and get some of this yellow poppy flower and a sore would come where it touched your hand, but I have some pity for you though you had none for me when I was in your hands.

title: Many Spirits Leading Westward
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 910.0, "meta.bpm": 80.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication
lyrics: Momoi [many] kokopa [spirits] honunewewa [westward] nuana [leading] ciamowa nakia [hanging] nye [my] moinak [heart] wangihona [strengthening]

title: In the Medicine Man's House
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 911.0, "meta.bpm": 76.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication
lyrics: Makai [Medicine man's] ki [house] wi [to] nye [me] vanem [led into] ordanyewa [left me inside] ki [house] nye [my] sikol [older brother] cukoni [owl] aan [feathers] bineminak [flying about] nyuicuna [singing]
lyrics_translation:
To the medicine man's house they have led me,
To the medicine man's house they have led me,
Inside the house they have brought me,
Elder Brother is there and owl feathers fly about,
The owl feathres sing in the air

title: Song Concerning the White Bees
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 912.0, "meta.bpm": 76.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication
lyrics: Thotha [white] momoveld [bees] can [over there] novanye [they will] nyeyopa [come out] hodoneko [in the west] miawa [they drop] kamova [yonder] hodoneko [in the west] vowi [toward] muko [distance] smamsim [plainly] thotham [shimmering white] yahusnuhuwa [fluttering]

title: Song Concerning the White Mountain
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 913.0, "meta.bpm": 72.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication
lyrics: Thoa [White] navavany [mountain] mumuko [far away] cyevut [earth] honginana [edge] kuka [stands] wathimohoi [beautiful] thamacoweka [it has] skuukcu [brilliant] thothama [white] kikiyona [arches]
lyrics_translation:
A white mountain is far at the west,
It stands beautiful,
It has brilliant white arches of light bending down toward the earth

title: We Smoke Together
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 914.0, "meta.bpm": 58.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication
lyrics: Roiinga [It was a sad thing] nehnona [you did to me] nawacik [cigarette] komoithan [smoke] mueda [inside of you] uhumapa [piling up]
lyrics_translation:
It was a sad thing you did,
It was a sad thing you did,
But now we smoke together,
The smoke will pile up inside us

title: The Meeting with Elder Brother
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 915.0, "meta.bpm": 72.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication
lyrics: Kunye kamhohimna [I was going there] cirvan [earth] honginana [end] himana [going] cirvan [earth] colikam [corner] Ithoi [Elder Brother] avuvumahaith [from two directions] nanamukim [we meet] hok [the] nye [my] moi [heart] thmiamoma [calling for help]
lyrics_translation:
Going alone to the earth end,
Going alone to the earth corner,
Elder Brother comes from the opposite direction
We meet and my heart is bounding within me

title: Song Concerning the Black Snake
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 916.0, "meta.bpm": 80.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication
lyrics: Aliwerci [(No meaning)] scuk [black] wahpamana [snake] hoduneko [west] vahwi [toward] susulinhimna [going erect] cinawikimtha [walking while moving] cinowang [mountain] mihivi [coiling around]
lyrics_translation:
A black snake goes toward the west,
It travels erect on its tail,
It sings as it goes toward the west, and coils around a mountain

title: The Rocks are Shaking
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 917.0, "meta.bpm": 76.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: Lyrics aligned with music in publication
lyrics: Vahvai [rocks] mongawa [shaking back and forth] onginunu [shaking him] wanur cinihonimur [he trembles] yoina [after] kahimukai [going] waamoh [farther] coingam [what can it mean?] nye [my] moi [heart] hohonemur [all gone]

title: Song of the Dawn
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1027.0, "meta.bpm": 58.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
It has been a long time since the light began to show, my brother
Just look, my brother,
Toward us the bows are brightening (referring to shafts of light bent above their heads like long bows)

title: The Sunrise
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1075.0, "meta.bpm": 126.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: Densmore does not report the location where this song was collected|Lyrics aligned with music in publication|On p. 114 Densmore reports a 'companion song' sung to the same melody (No 72)
lyrics:
Tharai [Sun] woceracima [rising] hokithab [at the side] kakatho [bows] yahaiwa [at the side] wuwucima [lying] hokithab [at the side] pur [the] mawithur [lion] mamata [babies] vupukumi [pink] thiamo [that is all]

Maratha [Moon] yutuna [setting] hokithab [at the side] pur [the] vapaku [canes] yahaiwa [at the side] wuwucima [lying] hokithab [at the side] kirohu [wild cat] mamatu [babies] yahaiwara [moving around] cucuwoi [uncertainly] kaiima [that is all]
lyrics_translation:
The sun is rising,
At either side a bow is lying,
Beside the bows are lion-babies,
The sky is pink, 
That is all

The moon is setting,
At either side are bamboos for arrow-making,
Beside the bamboos are wild-cat babies,
They walk uncertainly,
That is all.

title: In the Blue Night
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 932.0, "meta.bpm": 104.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
How shall I begin my song
In the blue night that is settling
I will sit here and begin my song

title: The Owl Feather
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 933.0, "meta.bpm": 69.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
The owl feather is rolling in this direction and beginning to sing.
The people listen and come to hear the owl feather
Rolling in this direction and beginning to sing.

title: They Come Hooting
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 934.0, "meta.bpm": 72.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
Early in the evening they come hooting about,
Some have small voices and some have large voices,
Some have voices of medium strength, hooting about.

title: In the Dark I Enter
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 935.0, "meta.bpm": 69.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
I can not make out what I see.
In the dark I enter.
I can not make out what I see.

title: His Heart is Almost Covered with Night
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 936.0, "meta.bpm": 104.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation: Poor old sister, you have cared for this man and you want to see him again, but now his heart is almost covered with night. There is just a little left.

title: I See Spirit-Tufts of White Feathers
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 937.0, "meta.bpm": 116.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
Ahead of me some owl feathers are lying,
I hear something running toward me,
They pass by me, and farther ahead
I see spirit-tufts of downy white feathers

title: Yonder Lies the Spirit Land
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 938.0, "meta.bpm": 112.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
Yonder lies the spirit land
Yonder the spirit land I see
Farther ahead, in front of me,
I see a spirit stand

title: Song of a Spirit
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 939.0, "meta.bpm": 88.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
A railroad running west,
He travels westward
When he gets a certain distance
He flaps his wings four times and turns back

title: We Will Join Them
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 940.0, "meta.bpm": 76.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
Yonder are spirits laughing and talking as though drunk.
They do the same things that we do.
Now we will join them.

title: My Feathers
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 941.0, "meta.bpm": 69.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
I pity you, my feathers
I pity you, my feathers, that they make fun of,
They must mean what they say,
Or perhaps they are crazy in their hearts

title: The Women are Singing
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 942.0, "meta.bpm": 69.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation: On the west side people are singing as though drunk. The women are singing as though they were drunk.

title: I Am Going to See the Land
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 951.0, "meta.bpm": 76.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
I am going far to see the land,
I am running far to see the land,
While back in my house the songs are intermingling

title: I Run Toward Ashes Hill
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 952.0, "meta.bpm": 112.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
Ashes Hill Mountain, toward it I am running,
I see the Ashes Hill come out clearer.

title: The Waters of the Spirits
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 953.0, "meta.bpm": 224.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
They brought me to the waters of the spirits.
In these waters the songs seem to be stringing out.

title: There I Will See the Dawn
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 943.0, "meta.bpm": 72.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
A low range of mountains, toward them I am running.
From the top of these mountains I will see the dawn.

title: I Run Toward the East
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 944.0, "meta.bpm": 116.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
I am not sure whether I am running west or east but I run on and on. 
I find that I am running east.

title: I Die Here
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 945.0, "meta.bpm": 208.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
I am dead here, I die and lie here,
I am dead here, I die and lie here,
Over on top of Vihuhput i had my dawn.

title: I Could See the Daylight Coming
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 946.0, "meta.bpm": 80.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
Black Butte is far. Below it I had my dawn.
I could see the daylight coming back of me.

title: The Dawn Approaches
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 947.0, "meta.bpm": 112.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
I am afraid it will be daylight before I reach the place to see.
I feel that the rays of the sun are striking me.

title: The Owl Feather is Looking for the Dawn
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 948.0, "meta.bpm": 76.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
The owl feather is likely to find the daylight.
He is looking for it.
He is looking to see the dawn shine red in the east.

title: The Morning Star
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 949.0, "meta.bpm": 108.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
The morning star is up.
I cross the mountains into the light of the sea.

title: Song of a Medicine Woman on Seeing that a Sick Person will Die
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 950.0, "meta.bpm": 106.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs used in the treatment of the sick", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
I think I have found out.
I think I have found out.
With the owl songs I have found out and I will return home.

title: Clouds Roll Toward Me
lyrics_translation: At the south side is water covered with green scum. Above it clouds roll toward me. I see this and think perhaps I will be caught in the rain, so I return home.

title: Great White Birds Over the Ocean
lyrics_translation: The great white birds that fly over the ocean came to our singing place, and over the ground they strung about.

title: The Dwelling Place of the Sun
lyrics_translation:
In the east is the dwelling place of the sun.
On top of this dwelling place the sun comes up and travels over our heads.
Below we travel.
I raise my right hand to the sun and then stroke my body in the ceremonial manner

title: Clouds are Approaching
lyrics: Siali [East] thanthanio [side] curcungi [clouds] kahowa [approaching] mumko [far] nurkai [rain far away] coko [raining here] thoahi [thunder]
lyrics_translation:
Clouds are standing in the east, they are approaching.
It rains in the distance.
Now it is raining here and the thunder rolls.

title: We are Singing in the Night
lyrics_translation:
Now as the night is over us we are singing the songs that were given to us.
You see the clouds beginning to form on top of the mountains.
They look like little white feathers.
You will see them shake like feathers in a wind.
Soon the raindrops will fall and make our country beautiful.

title: The Corn on Frog Mountain
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Frog Mountain, on top of it the corn comes up.
Eat it, eat it.

title: We are Making Wonderful Things
lyrics_translation:
(Referring to the images of things desired)
Now we sit with feathers tied on our heads,
We make wonderful things which you have not seen,
But we will show them to you some day.

title: Each Singer Wears a White Feather
lyrics_translation:
Each singer wears a white feather on his head,
Now it is nightfall,
We will sing through the night and perhaps we may do some good.

title: A Flaming Light in the East
lyrics_translation:
We see the light that brightens in the east,
It seems to turn to flame,
On the edge of it is something that looks like a white feather,
But we see that it is white clouds.

title: I Draw the Rain
comments: The location is written as "Pisinemak" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation: Here I am sitting and with my power I draw the south wind toward me. After the wind I draw the clouds, and after the clouds I draw the rain that makes the wild flowers grow on our home ground and look so beautiful.

title: Song Concerning the Lost Children
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Viinikut fields I got into.
I stayed there and my heart will be wet enough to last.

title: Song of the Watchers (a)
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
The eagle is flying above a in round circle and makes a round shadow on the ground.
I am walking around under that shadow.
The blue hawk is flying in a straight line and makes a straight shadow. 
Under that line I am running.

title: Song of the Watchers (b)
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
The sun doctor with his body painted in spots
At the edge of the earth I (the sun doctor) stand and see the ocean with its beautiful rolling waves.
I call up the beautiful white clouds.
I am glad to see them rise.

title: Song During Rain Divination
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
The eagle wing, under that I sat with the tiswin,
I drank that and I am well drunk.
The water that gathered on the blue hawk feathers at the end of the vasi, 
I drank of that and was staggered.

title: A Blue Wind
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
A blue wind.
I saw the tracks on the blue mountain.
Inside that mountain I found a bamboo plant growing.
From there I saw a seven-headed mountain running low from east to west.

title: Song After Drinking the Wine
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.

title: You Make Me Drink Red Water
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
A red water you made me drink,
When I was drunk I went around as though I would fall down,
I fell on the ground face downward.

title: The Songs Are Beginning
lyrics: Thahrai [Sun] honunim [going down] keerna [proper time] nurinuri [songs] rzurzonco [commencing] yohoh [women] kaicokaci [hearing] wowewahpahima [running towards] konsun [hastening] thathaman [on the ground] merliwa [they arrive]
lyrics_translation:
At sunset, the proper time for the beginning of the songs, they begin.
The women hear the song, and hasten to reach the place.
They arrive at the place

title: I Am Running Toward the Edge of the World
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
I am on my way running, 
I am an my way running,
Looking toward me is the edge of the world,
I am trying to reach it,
The edge of the world does not look far away,
To that I am on my way running.

title: White Blossoms on Baboquivari Mountain
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Baboquivari is there on the east side, 
It has white blossoms on it. 
Toward that mountain I am on my way,
I am running to join the singer.

title: Cottonwood Leaves Are Falling
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
The cottonwood leaves are falling and flying in the air,
On top of the remaining mountain they are flying around,
And falling as though they are wet.

title: The Morning Is Shining Upward
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Poor man, did you leave me and walk away?
The morning is shining upward,
To that I am going.

title: On Top of the Mountain the Wind Blows
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Blackish Mountain, he stands there like a "doctor mointain."
On top the wind blows out,
On top the wind blows out,
And on top the clouds go out and cover the whole world.

title: I Go Toward the East
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
I do not understand where I am going,
To Anakum I run and turn close to the village,
Going toward the east.

title: Cowaks, Come and Help Us Sing
lyrics_translation:
We stand and start the singing.
Cowaka, come out and help us sing.
We will keep you standing all night long and cure you.

title: Song Before an Expedition to Obtain Salt
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1010.0, "meta.bpm": 76.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs connected with expeditions to obtain salt", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
We are scraping the basket and singing,
We hear the echoes in all the mountains around us,
We will make a trip to the salt and are singing to make it easy for us to get it.

title: We Will Run Around the Salt Bed
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1011.0, "meta.bpm": 66.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs connected with expeditions to obtain salt", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
lyrics_translation:
We will run around the salt bed,
We will run so fast that the stars will seem to run,
In this way perhaps one of us may secure magic power.

title: The Wind Blows from the Sea
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1028.0, "meta.bpm": 76.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs connected with expeditions to obtain salt", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
By the sandy water I breathe in the odor of the sea,
From there the wind comes and blows over the world,
By the sandy water I breathe in the odor of the sea,
From there the clouds come and rain falls over the world.

title: The Rain on the Corn and the Squash
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1029.0, "meta.bpm": 63.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs connected with expeditions to obtain salt", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Under us the world spreads wide,
From that the corn comes up,
On the leaves the water moves in little drops,
Under us the mountain stands wide,
On that the squash comes up,
And the water spreads over the vines.

title: The Sun Rises Over the Mountain
other_fields: {"meta.catalogue_num": 1030.0, "meta.bpm": 54.0, "file.SOCIAL_FUNCTION": "songs connected with expeditions to obtain salt", "file.REG": "Southwest", "file.LANG": "Non-Tone", "file.LING_GROUP": "Uto-Aztecan"}
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.|Rasping sticks play unaccented eight notes
lyrics_translation:
A mountain called Hootho, on top of it the sun rises,
It seems to waver,
A mountain called Hootho, on top of it the sun sets

title: Yonder the Flames Leap Upward
lyrics: Hukia potha [I am] himukai [gone] peanyetho [I will not] jijivia [return] hukia nutha [I am] hupaiyu [somewhere] moot [dead] kamayu [yonder] kamhomuihim [flames] kukiwa [stand up]

title: Song Before Starting on the Warpath
lyrics_translation:
I am going to walk far, far.
I hope to have a fine morning somewhere.
I am going to run far, far.
I hope to have a good night somewhere.

title: The Apache Hid Behind Trees
lyrics_translation:
Yonder, near the enemy's country, stand many great trees behind which they hid.
They have retreated farther.
They act like children.
They hide behind the women or anything that will conceal them.

title: While We Drink the Wine
lyrics_translation:
We make wine.
With deliberation we took our revenge.
We make the scalp poles hop like crows while we drink the wine, but let us keep our self-control while we are rejoicing.

title: Opening Song of the War Camp
lyrics: Hodunye [night] gusma [coming down] thahewa [sitting] gutanih [in the night] kunyemaitha [my enemy] miatha [trying to locate]

title: Help Us Locate Our Enemies
lyrics_translation: Crow, hurry and come, sit down, help us locate our enemies

title: Song for the Enemy's Country
lyrics: Cyevut [the land] miawa [nearer] yuuld [appears] miawa [in sight nearer] nutha [we can see] nyemaitha [my enemies] miawa [nearer] yuuld [appear in sight]

title: Song to Bring the Clouds
lyrics: Cuwakiki [clouds] wumia [together] himtha [going] wumaci [with him] gamuko [far away] himtha [going] nyemaitha [my enemies] zazakali [staggering] nanaki [as if crazy]
lyrics_translation:
Heavy clouds going with him.
Clouds going far away.
Our enemies stagger as though drunk.

title: The Voice of the Herald
lyrics_translation:
When the morning starts and the sun comes up.
When the morning starts and the sun comes up.
At that time the voice of the herald sounds sweet.
It seems to be calling for me.

title: The Little Captive Children
lyrics_translation:
Men shouting "brother", men shouting "brother,"
Among the mountains they have taken little Apache children where the sun went down in sorrow,
All women, what shall we do to realize this?

title: You Beg for Food Like a Woman
lyrics_translation: Now you are sitting here, acting like a woman, begging for food like a woman. You said you were brave and painted yellow spots on your head like a man, but now you talk like a woman.

title: I Have Gone Through This Before You
lyrics_translation:
I have gone through all this before you,
I have run on the ountains and run on the plains with little food or clothing, 
But I think of my shield that I use when I run up to the Apache and kill him,
I want you all to feel that way.

title: Sing Louder
lyrics_translation:
Sing it so I will hear as you sing.
It is your own fault that will punish you for what you have done.

title: I Am Dancing
lyrics_translation:
I have jumped here and there.
While I am dancing I jump in another place.

title: A Place of Many Springs
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
I amrunning on the side of the east.
The people began to push us to where the land has many springs.
There is where they left us.

title: Song Concerning a Wounded Apache
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
(First set of words, supposed to be spoken by the Apache)
Near sunset time I fall down,
Near sunset time I fall down,
I am going almost like a drunken man.

(Second set of words, indicating where war cries were given)
It is toward evening (yell), he falls (yell),
It is toward evening,
He falls, he staggers like a drunken man (yell)

title: Opening Song of the Limo
lyrics_translation:
How did you kill?
Oh, how did you hang the scalp on the pole?

title: Song of the Limo
lyrics_translation:
I will go inside to warm.
There we will sit a while and rub our tired legs.

title: I Am Going to Another Part of Elder Brother's Land
lyrics_translation:
I am going to another part of Elder Brother's land,
I have reached the land,
With a handsome child (captive) I am returning

title: A Whirlwind Is Singing
lyrics_translation:
Where is that bird going, where is that bird going?
With that bird I whirl around, whirl around higher and higher,
Just before we touch the sky, the bird faints and falls to the earth.
(This song was said to be concerning the "wind-grandson-bird")

title: It Is the Woodpecker
lyrics_translation:
Who is that bird flying over there?
Oh, it is the woodpecker,
He does not seem to want to go anywhere,
He cries and pecks at a cactus

title: The Eagle Is Talking
lyrics_translation:
The eagle is on the highest point of rocks,
He is talking,
I was walking below and I heard the sound echo among the rocks.

title: We Must Run
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Now be ready, my poor brother, and we will start to run,
Now before us our nice ball goes far,
After it we run,
No matter what kind of ground there is,
We must run over it

title: Song for Success in a Race
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.

title: Opening Song of the Bat Dance
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
Now the songs are going to begin and I am going away.
All over the mountains and on top of the mountains I sing.
Ajo mountain, on top of it I am singing and walking around.

title: My Wings Make a Noise as I Fly
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation: The evening looked red and I came out. Into all the houses I went and my wings are making a noise as I fly around the house.

title: Dream Song of a Captive Woman
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation: When I got to the side of the mountain my heart began to give out.

title: I Wandered Away
lyrics_translation:
Where the mountain crosses.
On top of the mountain, I do not myself know where.
I wandered where my mind and my heart seemed to be lost.
I wandered away.

title: I Am Going to the Mountain
lyrics_translation:
Away off to the mountains where I am going.
I do not know where I am going

title: I Went to the Edge of the World
lyrics_translation: I went down to the edge of the world and from there I saw in the east where the morning was breaking. I saw white stripes.

title: The Thunder Sounds in the East
lyrics_translation:
Back in the east there is a sound like thunder.
There was a great sound in the east where the thunders were sounding.

title: White Mountain Birds were Singing
lyrics_translation: White mountain birds where singing sweetly in the east. It sounded like thunders where he was singing.

title: A Black Crow
lyrics_translation:
A crow came down from above to this earth,
A black crow came down from above to this earth,
He was jumping on me.

title: I Sat Under Santa Rita Mountains
lyrics_translation:
I was under Santa Rita Mountains.
I sat there and thought of things far away, in distant parts of the world.

title: Song for Success in Hunting
lyrics_translation: We sit here by our camp fire and start to sing our hunting song. I can clearly see the points of the deer's ears on top of the hill. We smoke the pihol flowers that make the night clear, so I can see the points of the deer's ears on the hill.

title: Song of an Unsuccessful Hunter
lyrics_translation:
I am walking a great deal.
I am sorry I can not find any game.
I saw lots of tracks, especially on the east side of the mountain, but I found nothing.

title: Lullaby
lyrics_translation:
Gisuk, black-headed gisuk.
Run and come so the baby's eyes will go to sleep.

title: The Squirrel and the Mesquite Beans
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation: Now the beans begin to appear on the mesquite trees. Ground squirrel does not want to wait until the beans are ripe, so he climbs the trees, gets the beans, and scatters them green under the tree.

title: The Robin Brings the Cold Wind
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation:
The robin spreads the green wind on us.
He spreads the coldest wind on us.
Now knock him down with a stick.

title: The Snow Is Falling
lyrics_translation:
No talking, no talking,
The snow is falling,
And the wind seems to be blowing backward (circling back again).

title: I Met a Mexican
lyrics_translation:
While I was running I met a Mexican who said,
"How do you do?"
While I was running I met a Mexican with a long beard who said,
"How do you do?"

title: The Pigeon and His Tiswin Lodge
comments: The location is written as "Vomari" by Densmore.
lyrics_translation: The pigeon pretended that he was setting up a tiswin lodge. The frog doctor drank his wine, got drunk and shouted, and pulled out his cloud.
